This implementation feels contorted.  Couldn't we do something like:

```python
if is_list:
    if len(value_pb) == 0:
        return NOne
    meanings = set([_get_meaning(sub_value_pb)
                   for sub_value_pb in value_pb.list_value])
    if len(meanings) > 1:
        raise ValueError("Mismatch")
    return list(meanings)[0]
if value_pb.HasField('meaning'):
    return value_pb.meaning
